H0.text: Time is the unit represented by the ounce, the pound, and the ton.

H1.text: Weight is the unit for the ounce, the pound, and the ton.

H2.text: Length is the unit of the ounce, the pound, and the ton.

H3.text: Distance is the unit of the ounce, the pound, and the ton.

A4.text: An ounce is any of several units of mass

A5.text: Ounce-force, a unit of force, one sixteenth of a pound-force

A6.text: The pound or pound-mass is a unit of mass

A7.text: The yard or the metre shall be the unit of measurement of length and the pound or the kilogram shall be the unit of measurement of mass

A8.text: Ton is a unit of measure of mass

A9.text: The displacement, essentially the weight, of a ship is traditionally expressed in long tons
